      "slug": "what-is-a-percent",
      "title": "What Is a Percent?",
      "concreteComparison": "A phone battery at $75\\%$ is 75 out of every 100 — three-quarters full. A test score of $90\\%$ is 90 right out of 100. **Percent** means 'out of 100', and the $\\%$ sign is shorthand for 'per hundred'.",
      "objective": "Understand percent as 'out of 100', and write a percent as a fraction over 100 and as a decimal.",
      "concept": [
        "**Percent** means 'per hundred'. $37\\%$ means **37 out of 100**, which is the fraction $\\frac{37}{100}$.",
        "Because it is already out of 100, a percent is the same as a **two-place decimal**: $37\\% = 0.37$.",
        "The whole is $100\\%$. Half is $50\\%$, a quarter is $25\\%$, and nothing is $0\\%$."
      ],
      "keyIdea": "Percent means out of 100: $n\\% = \\frac{n}{100} =$ the decimal with $n$ hundredths.",
      "facts": [
        {
          "title": "Percent = hundredths",
          "latex": "$37\\% = \\dfrac{37}{100} = 0.37$",
          "explanation": "Out of 100 is a fraction over 100 and a two-place decimal."
        }
      ],
      "workedExamples": [
        {
          "id": "pct-we1",
          "statement": "Write $37\\%$ as a fraction and a decimal.",
          "solution": "$37\\% = \\frac{37}{100} = 0.37$.",
          "check": ["Rational(37,100)*100 == 37"]
        },
        {
          "id": "pct-we2",
          "statement": "Write $50\\%$ as a fraction in simplest form.",
          "solution": "$50\\% = \\frac{50}{100} = \\frac{1}{2}$.",
          "check": ["Rational(50,100) == Rational(1,2)"]
        }
      ],
      "commonMistakes": [
        {
          "text": "Writing $9\\%$ as the decimal $0.9$.",
